      <p class="eyebrow">Emergency plumbing service</p>
      <h2>Fast help when water, drains, or fixtures become urgent</h2>
      <p>Emergency plumbing is different from a regular repair call. The first goal is to reduce water damage, stop the immediate problem where possible, and identify whether the issue is coming from a fixture, pipe, drain, water heater, sump pump, or sewer line.</p>
      <p>Fateh Plumbing & Electric helps with burst pipes, active leaks, overflowing toilets, sewer backups, blocked drains, leaking water heaters, failed sump pumps, and plumbing issues that affect a home, rental property, restaurant, retail unit, or small business.</p>
      <p>If you are not sure whether the issue is an emergency, call and describe what is happening. We will help you decide whether to shut off water, avoid the area, or schedule the next available service visit.</p>
    </div>
