  <section class="band faq">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Emergency plumber FAQ</p>
      <h2>Questions before calling an emergency plumber</h2>
    </div>
    <details><summary>Do you offer emergency plumbing in Brampton?</summary><p>Yes. Fateh Plumbing & Electric helps with urgent plumbing problems in Brampton, including burst pipes, active leaks, overflowing toilets, sewer backups, and no-hot-water situations.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What should I do before the plumber arrives?</summary><p>If it is safe, shut off the nearest fixture valve or the main water shutoff. Avoid standing water near electrical equipment, move valuables away from water, and call 647-980-9211.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Is a sewer backup an emergency?</summary><p>Yes. Stop using drains and fixtures connected to the backup, avoid contact with contaminated water, and call for plumbing help right away.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Is a leaking water heater urgent?</summary><p>A leaking tank can become urgent if water is spreading or the leak cannot be isolated. Shut off the water supply if safe and call for service.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Can you help with overflowing toilets?</summary><p>Yes. If possible, turn the small shutoff valve behind the toilet clockwise, stop flushing, and call if the toilet keeps overflowing or the home has no other working toilet.</p></details>
  </section>

